  abstract={The existing physical networks are rapidly developing, providing high bandwidth, low latency, and deterministic network services for industries such as industrial manufacturing, smart transportation, and remote collaboration. However, the existing network resource aggregation efficiency is relatively low, making it difficult to provide adaptive and differentiated services for users with different needs. To address this, we propose a resource aggregation and orchestration scheme based on network digital twinning. Firstly, we propose the system architecture of network digital twinning, which simulates and manages the network by establishing digital models, enabling flexible scalability and elastic pooling of resources. Secondly, we design network service mechanisms for different users, providing adaptive service solutions for enterprises of different scales and different types of businesses, thereby expanding the boundaries and market vitality of network services. Lastly, we propose a real-time resource orchestration mechanism that reduces computational complexity by leveraging the properties of optimal substructures. We validate the proposed architecture and algorithms in the digital twinning space, providing a new method for reducing network upgrade costs and improving resource utilization efficiency using network digital twinning.},
