  author={Chernoded, Andrei I. and Vasiliev, Victor A. and Tsyrkov, Alexander V.},
  booktitle={2021 International Conference on Quality Management, Transport and Information Security, Information Technologies (IT&QM&IS)}, 
  title={Application of Neural Networks in Production Control Tasks}, 
  year={2021},
  volume={},
  number={},
  pages={11-14},
  abstract={The solution of problems of management of discrete multi-nomenclature production is in many respects like the problems of optimization of systems defined by many parameters. Many different theories are devoted to these problems. Such problems are solved by mathematical methods of operations research, numerical minimization methods and many others. In our case, however, each new production management problem associated with the production of a product is not a separate problem but has some continuities. Each new production management system carries with it some aspects of previously used methods. In this regard, it is proposed to apply the apparatus of artificial intelligence to solve the problems of production management. Each new task of optimal choice of parameters for production management must be based on previously obtained solutions. It is proposed to create a teachable system, which gives a solution based on the accumulated “knowledge”. The proposed approach should increase the enterprise's mobility in making management decisions at all levels of management, throughout the entire life cycle. The models under development will be a functional extension of digital production processes.},
